article.headline: Lipscomb 83, Savannah State 64
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Shaun Durant, Brian Fisk and James Poindexter scored 13 points each to lead Lipscomb to an 83-64 victory Tuesday over winless Savannah State. Lipscomb (1-1) trailed only 2-0, led 37-23 at halftime and twice led by 27 points late in the game. Savannah State (0-4) went almost 12 minutes without scoring after making the first basket of the game. The Tigers were led by Donald Carson and Mark Williams who had 12 points each. Cameron Robinson added 12 points for Lipscomb and Brandon Hartwell and Labrian Lyons scored 11 each. The Tigers shot 40 percent from the floor and made only 4-of-21 3-pointers. Lipscomb hit 48.2 percent. The Bisons had a 43-28 rebounding edge.
